    FilesetItem
    Output of /usr/bin/lslpp -l FilesetName.
    FilesetObject
    The fileset_object is used by a fileset_test to define the fileset to be evaluated.
    FilesetState
    The fileset_state defines the different information associated with filesets installed on the system.
    FilesetTest
    The fileset_test is used to check information associated with different filesets installed on the system.
    FixItem
    From /usr/sbin/instfix -iavk APARNum Command.
    FixObject
    The fix_object is used by a fix test to define the specific fix to be evaluated.
    FixState
    The fix_state defines the different information associated with a specific fix installed on the system.
    FixTest
    The fix test is used to check information associated with different fixes installed on the system.
    InterimFixItem
    From emgr -l -u VUID Command.
    InterimFixObject
    The interim_fix_object is used by a interim_fix_test to define the specific fix to be evaluated.
    InterimFixState
    The interim_fix_state defines the different information associated with a specific interim fix installed on the system.
    InterimFixTest
    The interim fix test is used to check information associated with different interim or emergency fixes installed on the system.
    NoItem
    The no_item is used to hold information related to the /usr/sbin/no command and the tunable parameters it manages.
    NoObject
    The no_object is used by a no_test to define the specific parameter to be evaluated.
    NoState
    The no_state defines the different information associated with a specific call to /usr/sbin/no.
    NoTest
    The no test is used to check information related to the /usr/sbin/no command and the parameters it manages.
    OsLevelItem
    Information about the release and maintenance level of AIX operating system.
    OsLevelObject
    The oslevel_object is used by an oslevel test to define those objects to be evaluated based on a specified state.
    OsLevelState
    The oslevel_state defines the information about maintenance level (system version).
    OsLevelTest
    The oslevel test reveals information about the release and maintenance level of AIX operating system.
